# How to save the results
Save the result to {{hooksPath}} as strict JSON with this shape:
{
  "generations": [
    {
      "id": "gen-001",
      "createdAt": "ISO-8601",
      "options": [
        { "id": "hook-001", "text": "..." }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
Validation rules:
- Output valid JSON only. No markdown fences, comments, prose, or trailing commas.
- generations must be an array.
- Every generation needs a non-empty id, valid createdAt timestamp, and a non-empty options array.
- Every option needs only a non-empty id and text.
- Do not add any other fields to generations or individual hooks.
- If the file already exists, read it first and append a new generation instead of overwriting earlier generations.

## Use a temporary file first
You should not reference previously generated hooks, if any exist, when writing new hooks. To prevent you from doing this, do not read from {{hooksPath}} before you write the new hooks. Write the new hooks to a temporary file first, and then reference that temporary file and write the new hooks to {{hooksPath}}, so that you don't ever need to read {{hooskPath}} before writing your hooks, so that you can remain unbiased by previously generated hooks when writing new ones.
